<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/179936-which-edition-happens-to-include-the-best">Which edition happens to include the best critical apparatus such as endnotes? Oxford World&#39;s Classics edited by Ian Duncan or Penguin Classics edited by Karl Miller? (I don&#39;t believe that the NYRB edition includes endnotes.) Does anyone own both and therefore able to offer a comparison? Thank you in advance...</a>
</div>
