  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2356248150" />
    <a title="DeAnna Knippling" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3166570-deanna-knippling"><img alt="DeAnna Knippling" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442526565p2/3166570.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2356248150?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="DeAnna Knippling" class="user" itemprop="url" name="DeAnna Knippling" href="/user/show/3166570-deanna-knippling">DeAnna Knippling</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3166570-deanna-knippling?shelf=100-best-horror-books-kim-newman">100-best-horror-books-kim-newman</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2356248150" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2935206305355963184">A religious man, assured of his salvation by a hypocrite, partakes of evil. But is the evil straight from the devil, or a product of his own deranged mind?<br/><br/>This was sophisticated and compelling, a frame story surrounding the diary of a Calvinist spoiled brat, completely convinced that he can do no wrong. What is real is difficult to suss out, but as his life collapses around him, he refuses humility and friendship. What need has he of those things? He is already saved.<br/><br/>The ending is a wink and a n</span>
  <span id="freeText2935206305355963184" style="display:none">A religious man, assured of his salvation by a hypocrite, partakes of evil. But is the evil straight from the devil, or a product of his own deranged mind?<br /><br />This was sophisticated and compelling, a frame story surrounding the diary of a Calvinist spoiled brat, completely convinced that he can do no wrong. What is real is difficult to suss out, but as his life collapses around him, he refuses humility and friendship. What need has he of those things? He is already saved.<br /><br />The ending is a wink and a nudge to the reader. Fun stuff.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2935206305355963184" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
